M7 is complete. Commit `5730e78` closes the `session-memory-dream` initiative.

**What shipped in this commit:**
- `simple-agent memory dream` CLI subcommand (dry-run default, `--apply`, `--force`, `--provider openai`)
- `--dream-on-exit` REPL flag with one-shot guard and `_exit_session()` covering all exit paths
- `dream_runs / dream_merged / dream_pruned` counters in `MetricsCollector`
- `record_consolidation()` in `consolidation_lock.py` called inside `consolidate()` (gate+run+stamp self-contained)
- ADR-0005 documenting the no-cron divergence
- CLAUDE.md per-file summaries for all 5 touched modules + Current Limitations bullet
- `tests/test_memory_cli_dream.py`: 13 tests covering all 8 required scenarios
- pytest: 1000 → 1013 | mypy: clean | ruff: clean
